-- Santander UK says will meet next week to pick new CEO
-- By Steve Slater
-- Wed Sep 10, 2014 12:01PM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 10 (Reuters) - Santander UK said its board would meet next week to pick a new chief executive after current CEO Ana Botin was chosen as chairwoman of Santander Group <SAN.MC> following the death of her father. [ID:nL5N0RB0V8]

Santander's British bank said Nathan Bostock, its deputy CEO who only joined the bank last month, would be responsible for overseeing operations and strategy in the transition phase.